{"cursor":"7653","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Mark Friedman image = Mark Friedman 2010.jpg caption = Mark Friedman in\n| 2010 birth_date = 1948 birth_place = residence = Santa\n| Fe, New Mexico nationality = American alma_mater = Lehigh University,\n| Bethlehem, Pennsylvania occupation = Author, \"Trying Hard Is Not Good Enough\";\n| Director, Fiscal Policy Studies Institute; Senior Fellow, Center for the Study\n| of Social Policy title = spouse = Terry Wilson children = Megan, Julie and\n| Aaron footnotes =\n}}\n\n'Mark Friedman' is the Director of the Fiscal Policy Studies Institute in Santa\nFe, New Mexico, best known for his international work on Results-Based\nAccountability (RBA), also known in the UK and Australia as Outcomes-Based\nAccountability TM (OBA), a framework for turning data into action. He\nis also the author of the book Trying Hard Is Not Good Enough: How to Produce\nMeasurable Improvements for Customers and Communities. The RBA approach has been\napplied to improve services in over 40 US states and countries including\nAustralia, Canada, Ireland, New Zealand, the Netherlands, Norway and the\nUK.\n","linknr":163,"url":"Mark_Friedman_(FPSI)","recorded":1364128448,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Mark_Friedman_(author)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Mark_Friedman_(author)&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Mark_Friedman_(author)","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site